revision.text:
{{Infobox sportsperson | name = Amadou Camara | image = | imagesize = | caption = | nationality = Guinean | sport = [[Swimming at the Summer Olympics|Swimming]] | event = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1994|09|10|df=yes}} | birth_place = | height = 1.63 m | weight =69 kg | country = {{flag|Guinea}} | pb = | show-medals = | medaltemplates = }} '''Amadou Camara''' (born 10 September 1994)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/amadou-camara |title=Amadou Camara |publisher=Rio 2016 |accessdate=8 August 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806082719/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/amadou-camara |archivedate= 6 August 2016 |df= }}</ref> is a Guinean [[Swimming at the Summer Olympics|Olympic swimmer]].
==Career== He represented his country at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Men's 50 metre freestyle|Men's 50 metre freestyle]] event where he ranked at #78 with a time of 27.35 seconds. He did not advance to the semifinals.
Amadou Camara did not return to Guinea after the 2016 Summer Olympics in Brazil, having disappeared 48 hours before the team's scheduled departure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/olympics/la-sp-oly-rio-2016-two-guinea-athletes-do-not-return-home-1472317295-htmlstory.html|title=Two Guinea athletes do not return home after Rio Olympics|last=Press|first=Associated|website=latimes.com|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref>
