===Ireland (Republic of)=== Since the 1980s, it is customary for the [[Taoiseach]] of the day to visit the White House on [[Saint Patrick's Day]] and present the President with a bowl of [[shamrock]].<ref name="CroninAdair2006">{{cite book|last1=Cronin|first1=Mike|last2=Adair|first2=Daryl|title=The Wearing of the Green: A History of St Patrick's Day|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-5Y5A-emQJgC&pg=PA216|accessdate=June 20, 2016|year=2006|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=9780415359122|pages=216–226}}</ref><ref name="O'TooleDooney2009">{{cite book|last1=O'Toole|first1=John|last2=Dooney|first2=Sean|title=Irish Government Today|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EeX4AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT39|accessdate=June 20, 2016|date=July 24, 2009|publisher=Gill Books|isbn=9780717155347|page=39|chapter=Ministers and their Departments; Journeys abroad}}</ref>
