{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
'''Taski Etoka''' (also '''Mingatuska''', '''Tuskeatoka''') (died 1794)  was the leader of the [[Chickasaw Nation]] since mid-1780s. He was signator (along with [[Piomingo]] and [[Lotapaia]]) of the [[Treaty of Hopewell]], January 1786.<ref name=kings>[http://www.chickasaw.net/site06/heritage/print/250_1052.htm, "The Last of the Chickasaw Kings"]</ref>

Taski Etoka was succeeded by [[Chinubbee]], his brother.<ref name=kings/>

