{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Zeki Majed | image = ZekiMajedVienna.png | caption = Zeki Majed at [[Stephansplatz, Vienna]]. | birth_name = Zeki Anwar Majed | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|11|13}} | birth_place = [[Sofia]], [[Bulgaria]] | nationality = [[Kurdistan|Kurdish]] | occupation = [[Filmmaker]], [[Poet]] }}
'''Zeki Majed''' (born November 13, 1996) is a Kurdish [[filmmaker]] and [[poet]]. He was born and raised in [[Sofia]], [[Bulgaria]].
==Biography==
Majed was 14, the conflict in [[Syria]] began, quickly spreading to [[Aleppo]], which was a city that Majed spent a large portion of his childhood in. The demise of the city, was the reason he started to write. His first poem ''Eyes Never Dry'', won first prize at Pendle War Poetry Competition. As the war progressed he wrote more about the [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] fight, often writing about the female fighters, the [[Women's Protection Units]]. He wrote in a poem "(In a war) where we are deserted by an entire world, love is water for a thirsty soul." He wrote multiple love poems, praising women. A [[poem]] he wrote, ''Brave Woman''<ref name="poetrysoup">{{cite web|url=https://www.poetrysoup.com/poem/brave_woman_695295|publisher=poetrysoup.com|title=Brave Woman - Poem by Zeki Majed|accessdate=6 April 2017}}</ref> was read at [[St Margaret's, Westminster]], by [[Glenys Kinnock, Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead]] in memory of [[British MP]], [[Jo Cox]].<ref name="westminster-abbey">{{cite web|url=http://www.westminster-abbey.org/press/news/2016/june/jo-cox-mp-remembered-at-st-margarets-service|publisher=westminster-abbey.org|title=Westminster Abbey &raquo; Jo Cox MP remembered at St Margaret’s Service|accessdate=6 April 2017}}</ref>
